This paper proposes a novel approach for learning feature relations and data representations in an end-to-end manner using a self-attention graph network. The paper focuses on the application of this approach to machine learning, specifically in the context of variational autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
